Timothy Wall wrote:

&gt; Do a wait on a shared object; when all events have been fired, do a 
&gt; notify.  On the original wait, set your max timeout, e.g.
&gt; 
&gt; final Object lock = new Object();
&gt; synchronized(lock) {
&gt;       lock.wait(TIMEOUT_INTERVAL);
&gt; }
&gt; assertEquals(eventsExpected, eventsReceived);
&gt; 
&gt; On your event-listening thread:
&gt; 
&gt; synchronized(lock) {
&gt;       // after all events have been sent
&gt;       lock.notifyAll();
&gt; }

I have to admit that my multithreading skills are atrocious. This is the 
first time I ever understood multithreaded programming in Java. Thank you.
